Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of estimating unknown parameters of a population based on observations of random variables. This falls under the domain of statistical inference and machine learning, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.IT (Information Theory) is a likely category as the paper discusses the information-theoretic lower bound on the estimation error. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category as the paper proposes a learning algorithm to estimate the parameters. cs.ST (Statistics) is another likely category as the paper deals with statistical inference. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper applies the algorithm to datasets from social and sports domains. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper discusses the computational complexity of the algorithm.
